This paper is about automatic dialog act recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) research (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper explores the use of context information, which is relevant to the subfield of social dynamics (cs.SD) in NLP. Finally, the paper discusses the use of multiple token segment representations, which could be relevant to the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE) in machine learning.
